h as literally billions of dollars are burnt quarter after quarter on training increasingly giant and complicated models to eek out bits of performance and the choice of optimizer algorithm for your AI training can have tremendous effects on wasted resources unless you can have confidence that your algorithm of choice is the best one to put the weight of tremendous training runs onto."}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("div",{className:"centered-item-holder",children:[/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("img",{src:"/assets/pics/gradient_descent.webp",alt:"Gradient Descent",style:{maxWidth:"960px",maxHeight:"550px"}}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("p",{className:"small-text",style:{maxWidth:"600px"},children:"The Trillion dollar challenge: You're dropped with $10B of GPUs into the mountains without a map and racing against the clock to navigate down to the valley below..."})]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("p",{children:["If you aren't deeply emeshed into AI training it would be worthwhile to provide a brief description of what an optimizer even serves to do in the first place: Optimizer algorithms are responsible for taking ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("i",{children:"how wrong"})," an AI is at the task it's trying to get good at and translating that measurement of error into how far each and every parameter dial in your AI model should be turned to try and ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("i",{children:"bring that error down"}),". Pretty important work."]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("p",{children:"Technically, when training a model we're given:"}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("ol",{children:[/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("li",{children:["A Dataset"," ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\( D = \\{(x_i,y_i)\\}^{N}_{i=1} \\)`})," ","where ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(x_i\\)`})," are input features and ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(y_i\\)`})," are target labels."]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("li",{children:["A Model ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(f(x, \\theta)\\)`})," with parameters ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(\\theta\\)`}),"."]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("li",{children:["A Loss function"," ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(L(f(x, \\theta), y)\\)`})," that measures the difference between predicted output"," ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\( f(x, \\theta) \\)`})," and the true output ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\(y\\)`}),"."]})]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsxs("p",{children:["The goal is then to find the optimal parameters"," ",/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{inline:true,children:`\\( \\theta^{*} \\)`})," that minimizes the loss function over the dataset:"]}),/*#__PURE__*/_jsx("p",{children:/*#__PURE__*/_jsx(MathJax,{block:true,dynamic:true,children:`\\[ \\theta^* = \\arg\\min_{\\theta} \\frac{1}{N} \\sum_{i=1}^N
